children: Sock It 2 Me is one of Missy biggest hits in 1997 through 1998, the video is also known for its interesting concept. It was written by Shawntae Harris, William Hart, Thom Bell and producer Timothy “Timbaland” Mosley for her debut album Supa Dupa Fly (1997) and released as the album’s second single in a slightly re-recorded form. The song’s beat directly samples the 1968 single “Ready or Not Here I Come (Can’t Hide from Love)” by the Delfonics.

children: “The Rain” is as impressionistic as any lyric in rap; it sets a numinous mood. Furthermore,

, and it also spawned her first music video. Timbaland produced and co-wrote the song and appeared in the video (the beginning of Elliott’s longtime collaboration with director Hype Williams until he was replaced by Dave Meyers). Elliott played up her size in the video by wearing an enormous inflated trash bag – a “screw you” to all the execs who told her she was too fat to make it in the music business.
